### Description

I create a component dynamically based on a given input via `createComponent` function

```ts
constructor() {
    afterNextRender({
      write: () => {
        if (!this.externalUse) return;

        // Create scroll content wrapper
        this.createContentWrapper(this.actualContentElement);

        // Initialize viewport
        this.viewport.init(this.nativeElement, this.actualContentRef.location.nativeElement, this.spacerElement);
      }
    })
  }

  createContentWrapper(hostElement: HTMLElement): void {
      // Attach content wrapper component
    this.actualContentRef = createComponent(ContentWrapper, {
      hostElement,
      elementInjector: this.injector,
      environmentInjector: this.appRef.injector
    });

     this.appRef.attachView(this.actualContentRef.hostView);
  }
```

Everything works properly in the app at runtime, however, when I try to test in Karma, it always fail. the created component is never rendered inside the test. but the reference is defined.

```ts
expect(component.actualContentRef.location.nativeElement.parentElement).toBe(component.nativeElement);
```
The `parentElement` here is null in the test but in the app it is defined as expected!

I notice that this happens only when I create the component dynamically, but when I used the component using Angular template the test was rendering the component.

Why is this happening?


